      "message": "I\u0027ve made a comment on this helper function to document that it throws.\n\nThe 2 usages of it in the EMConfig constructor are intended to not be caught since the constructor itself also throws on error.\n\nFor a non-throwing way to construct it, `fromJson` can be used. I documented that as the *preferred* function and keeping the throwing one to avoid verbosity/workarounds in testcases.\n\nLet me know if you still prefer this function to not throw, but it will result in extra wrapper code to re-throw in the constructor.\n\nAlternatively we can model it as \u0027nothing throws\u0027 depending on your preference.",
